Title: Automation May Peril Job Growth: O.E.C.D. Wary Even if Output Rises in 1980's The Decade Ahead Major Consequences 'Jobless Growth' Specter Seen For West in 1980's Outlook for France Further Pessimism
Abstract: PARIS, July 4--The United States and other Western industrial countries may face a period of "jobless growth" in the 1980's, even if President Carter and other nations' leaders succeed in their declared aim of expanding business investment and ending the world recession.
